Part 2, Step 3 (Similarity Scores)

Load and clean data

data_full <- read_csv("datafiles/Sample 3.csv")

data <- subset(data_full, Filter==0 & trait=="dominant")

Graphing results

Organize data

data_mean <- data %>%
  summarize_at(vars(BM_BW:AMO_AWO), mean)

data_sd <- data %>%
  summarize_at(vars(BM_BW:AMO_AWO), sd)

data_graph <- data.frame(t(rbind(data_mean, data_sd)))
names(data_graph) <- c("mean", "SD")

data_graph$SE <- data_graph$SD/sqrt(nrow(data))
data_graph$LCI <- data_graph$mean - 1.96*data_graph$SE
data_graph$UCI <- data_graph$mean + 1.96*data_graph$SE
data_graph$Comparison <- row.names(data_graph)

data_graph$Comparison <- fct_inorder(data_graph$Comparison)

data_graph$RaceGender <- c("Black Man\nBlack Woman", "Black Man\nAsian Man", "Black Man\nAsian Woman",
                          "Black Woman\nAsian Man", "Black Woman\nAsian Woman", "Asian Man\nAsian Woman",
                          "Black Man\nBlack Woman", "Black Man\nAsian Man", "Black Man\nAsian Woman",
                          "Black Woman\nAsian Man", "Black Woman\nAsian Woman", "Asian Man\nAsian Woman")

data_graph$RaceGender <- fct_inorder(data_graph$RaceGender)

data_graph_labels <- c("Black Man\nBlack Woman", "Black Man\nAsian Man", "Black Man\nAsian Woman",
                          "Black Woman\nAsian Man", "Black Woman\nAsian Woman", "Asian Man\nAsian Woman")

data_graph$Occupation <- ifelse(str_detect(data_graph$Comparison, "O") == TRUE, "Occupation", "No Occupation")

Graph main similarity comparisons

sim_graph <- ggplot(data_graph, aes(group = fct_rev(Occupation), x = RaceGender, y = mean, ymin = LCI, ymax = UCI, color = fct_rev(Occupation))) +
  geom_errorbar(width=0,cex=1, position = position_dodge(width = .3)) +
  geom_point(size=2.5, position = position_dodge(width = .3)) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(legend.position = "none",
        panel.grid.major.x = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.minor.y = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.minor.x = element_blank(),
        axis.text.x = element_text(size=15),
        axis.text.y = element_text(size=14),
        axis.title.x = element_blank(),
        axis.title.y = element_text(size=16)) +
  scale_x_discrete(labels=data_graph_labels) +
  ylab("Mean Similarity Score") +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks=c(3.5, 4, 4.5, 5, 5.5), limits=c(3.4, 5.8)) +
  scale_color_manual(values=c("indianred1", "royalblue3"))

Create tidy summaries of t-tests for graphing

ttest_graph <- rbind(tidy(Test1), tidy(Test2), tidy(Test3), tidy(Test4), tidy(Test5), tidy(Test6))

ttest_graph$Comparison <- c("Black Man\nBlack Woman", "Black Man\nAsian Man", "Black Man\nAsian Woman",
                          "Black Woman\nAsian Man", "Black Woman\nAsian Woman", "Asian Man\nAsian Woman")

ttest_graph$Comparison <- fct_inorder(ttest_graph$Comparison)

Create graph of difference scores with 95% CIs

diff_graph <- ggplot(ttest_graph, aes(x = Comparison, y = estimate, ymin = conf.low, ymax = conf.high)) +
  geom_errorbar(width=0,cex=1, color="slateblue4") +
  geom_point(size=2.5, color="slateblue4") +
  geom_hline(yintercept=0) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(legend.position = "none",
        panel.grid.major.x = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.minor.y = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.minor.x = element_blank(),
        axis.text.x = element_blank(),
        axis.text.y = element_text(size=14),
        axis.title.x = element_blank(),
        axis.title.y = element_text(size=16)) +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks=c(0, .5, 1, 1.5), limits=c(-.2, 1.6)) +
  ylab("Difference (With  Without)")

Combine with patchwork

combined_graph <- sim_graph + diff_graph + plot_layout(ncol=1) + plot_annotation(title = "Dominance Similarity Scores <span style='color:indianred1;'>With</span> and <span style='color:royalblue3;'>Without</span> Occupation (and Their <span style='color:slateblue4;'>Difference</span>)", theme = theme(plot.title = element_markdown(lineheight = 1.1, size = 18, hjust=.5)))

ggsave("figures/combined_p2_dominant.jpg", height=8, width=10, unit="in", dpi=600)
